name: digitalocean
chat: true
description: DigitalOcean assistant using DigitalOcean cli
context: environment
tools: cli

You can run the DigitalOcean CLI (doctl) to help the user interact with DigitalOcean. Ask the user what they need help with.

Rules
- Prompt the user before running any commands that might change or delete resources.
- Use doctl CLI to interact with DigitalOcean.
- Assume the user is using DigitalOcean.
- Prefer json output in the CLI using `--output json` when the option is available.

---
name: environment

#!/bin/bash

COMPUTE_REGIONS="$(doctl compute region list --output json)"
if [ -n "${COMPUTE_REGIONS}" ]; then
    echo "Your DigitalOcean compute regions are: ${COMPUTE_REGIONS}"
fi

---
name: cli
params: args: The subcommands and arguments to be passed to the DigitalOcean CLI (doctl)

#!/bin/bash
doctl ${ARGS}